# ============================================================
# File: .gitignore
# Purpose: Tell Git which files and folders to ignore.
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Git tracks files that belong to the project, i.e., files that we write.
# This file lists things that do NOT need to be tracked:
# system files, temporary files, and auto-generated build output.
#
# Think of it as a list of "these are not files we wrote".
# ============================================================

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# .gitignore for a Node / Vite / TypeScript project
# ------------------------------------------------------------

# Local environment and build output
dist/
.temp/
.cache/
.env
.env.*.local
!.env.example

# Vite specific
.vite/

# TypeScript
*.tsbuildinfo

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# macOS system files
# ------------------------------------------------------------

.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

# macOS resource forks and thumbnails
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
Icon\r
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# VS Code settings and extensions
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# The .vscode folder holds local editor settings.
# Most of the files inside are personal or computer-specific
# and should NOT be shared (for example, window sizes, last open files, etc.).
#
# However, two files are useful for everyone working on the project:
#   settings.json - contains shared workspace settings
#   extensions.json - contains recommended VS Code extensions
#
# The pattern below ignores everything in .vscode/
# but then re-includes only those two shared files.
#
# It means: ignore everything in .vscode,
# except settings.json and extensions.json.
# ------

.vscode/*
!.vscode/settings.json
!.vscode/extensions.json

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Logs and temporary files
# ------------------------------------------------------------

npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
lerna-debug.log*
*.log

# Crash reports
report.[0-9]*.[0-9]*.[0-9]*.[0-9]*.json

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional caches (safe to delete anytime)
# ------------------------------------------------------------

*.local
.cache/
*.tmp
*.bak

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# OS backup or metadata files
# ------------------------------------------------------------

*.swp
*.swo
*~
*.orig
*.rej

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# GitHub Pages deployment artifacts
# ------------------------------------------------------------

# Pages build artifacts (if deploying from Actions)
*.tar.gz
pages-artifact/
pages-build/
